\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16733626 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 
Well you knew by their attitude to you - what they were. If a person was friendly you treated 'em friendly. If there was - what I call aggravating you - 
you - you give 'em the cold shoulder, you didn't want to speak to 'em any more did you. See, if people spoke to you respectfully - you see - you answered them the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7229527 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 
Were there any people you would address as sir or madam, any special type of person who you would ever address like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16733626 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 
Oh yes, like - if you knew - for instance a policeman's wife or anyone like that, you see, you respect - spoke respectful to 'em. Or publican, he was a big pot, the publican. You spoke respectful to him. Or any
 - any tradesman - there was plenty of good old English tradesman about, had - grocers shops and - lord knows what they were, and you was obliged to speak respectful to 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7229527 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 Were you ever brought up to touch your cap to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16733626 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 Oh - well - you 
was always told to be polite, as much as you could, you know. Be respectful, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7229527 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 
Can you remember if people were respectful to your parents, would your parents be called sir or madam by anybody?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16733626 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 Well - that I don't know but I have had it calle
d to me lots of times even, and I'm younger than them, but - that was a matter of - what - where you went you see. You went in different districts, the children were of a different variety. See, you went - down as I say the waterside, the children - were 
-
 had a - a bit of a rough tongue, you see. Some peoples like - they used to say the Billingsgate language, they always swore. They didn't know nothing else. They don't know they're swearing. Them people - the poor element where they swore - they swore at 
the children and that, they didn't know they was swearing. That was - they got used to that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7229527 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 Were you allowed to swear in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16733626 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 
No. Oh no, no. No, no, you would get a clump - over my sisters you see. You mustn't swear. That wouldn't be allowed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7229527 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 And in this part of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} who would be considered the most important people Possibly the people who you would respect most.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16733626 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 
Doctors or anyone like that or - sanitary inspectors or anybody like that you see. They were - police was r
espect - you had to be respectful. Although you - you couldn't - be otherwise because they wouldn't allow you to be. If you was disrespectful to 'em you'd soon get a - a clump, they didn't allow that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7229527 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 What about clergymen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16733626 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 Clergymen was the same. You had to be respectful to clergymen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7229527 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 
Would you come into contact with clergymen, would they come to your house to visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16733626 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 
Well - you - you - you knew - in your own district you knew most of the clergyman. You knew the man from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Christchurch{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} or
 John Knox's or that - as - when you're young. And - they used to have any little activities like you - had like sport activities, if the local clergymen took part in it, they had one here in St Dunstans once, and he was called the Pied Parson. You see, h
e
 was an old boxer. And they told me after, later years, he went away - down the West of England - and these here tramps used to come there for a - something to eat you know, casual ward, like a casual ward, and he used to make 'em have the gloves on with 
him and give 'em a good - give 'em a pounding, then feed 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7229527 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 That's a very christian attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16733626 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 
That was a - I - I remember it. Yes, he - the fighting parson. Yes, he - he was a - star turn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7229527 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 For what reasons would these people be considered important at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16733626 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 What people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7229527 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 The ones you mentioned, the doctors, the clergymen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16733626 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 
Well they was above - a station above you weren't they. See a doctor was a - personality wasn't he. You see, there - there wasn't no - when I was a b
oy there was no health service like there is today, that - I remember that Act coming out, it was about 19 - 10 or - or '12, something like that, when the insurance act first came out. I was only young - lad I know. Used to have to pay - fourpence - the -
 the guv'nor paid threepence and you paid fourpence, out your first day's work was stopped. If you started work on the Monday so they stopped you fourpence for - insurance stamp, that was the beginning of the - insurance act.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7229527 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 So can you remember your family having to pay for a doctor's services?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16733626 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 
My parents never. I don't think my parents paid much. I don't think my dad ever had - any health - benefits or anything like that or my mum. Anything from the health insurance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7229527 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 Did they ever have to see a doctor can you remember?
