 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Bridge{\*\xmlclose}, and then {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Stratford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And then you went on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Manor{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and then Ilford. But there was one, two, three - say about - from here to Ilford be about five or 
six stops where they're liable to put their hand up a policeman, but on a bike you was confident, you rode by, you never - you wouldn't have accident, you - just rode round the vehicle what you wanted and go on, there was only horses on that road that tim
e, wasn't no motors. The danger came for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13831914\charrsid66970 cyclists}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2968889\charrsid66970 
